The paper discusses the use of machine learning methods for event classification, which is a common topic in the sub-field of machine learning (cs.LG). The methods used involve convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of simulated data, which suggests a numerical analysis (cs.NA) component. Additionally, the use of machine learning for classification is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and the application of these methods to experimental data falls under the sub-field of scientific computing (cs.SI).
